    answer: "For optimal outdoor installation: 1) Choose locations with proper weather protection (IP67-rated enclosures included). 2) Ensure mounting surfaces can support 3x the camera weight. 3) Maintain clearance from trees/bushes (minimum 3 feet). 4) Use provided waterproof cable glands for all connections. 5) Consider sun position to avoid glare. 6) For PoE installations, use outdoor-rated Ethernet cables with proper surge protection. We recommend professional installation for heights above 10 feet. The included mounting template helps with precise positioning and cable routing."
  },
