    answer: "Recommended maintenance schedule: Weekly: Check system alerts and storage status. Monthly: Clean camera lenses with microfiber cloth, verify weather seals, test night vision. Quarterly: Update firmware, inspect cables/connections, verify backup systems. Annually: Professional inspection for large installations. For IR cameras: periodically check for spider webs near lenses. Our devices include self-diagnostic tools accessible via the web interface that monitor system health, temperature, and component status. Always power down equipment before cleaning and use only manufacturer-approved accessories."
